Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.84,0:00:05.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我叫乌特雷德，乌特雷德之子\N{\rEnglish}My name is uhtred, son of uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.48,0:00:07.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我生来便是诺森布里亚的郡长\N{\rEnglish}I was born an ealdorman of northumbria.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.12,0:00:10.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}贝班堡的正统继承人\N{\rEnglish}The rightful heir to bebbanburg.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.92,0:00:14.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但命运安排我在丹麦人中长大\N{\rEnglish}But fate decreed I would be raised as a Dane.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.00,0:00:18.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那就是我的生活\N{\rEnglish}That was my life
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.84,0:00:21.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}直到我的家人惨遭杀害\N{\rEnglish}until my family was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.88,0:00:30.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}外面传言说称我是罪魁祸首\N{\rEnglish}Word was spread that I was to blame.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.56,0:00:33.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}一个撒克逊奴隶，在婚宴上杀了自己的主人\N{\rEnglish}A Saxon slave, he killed his master at a wedding party.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.20,0:00:39.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}于是，我和布丽达逃往威塞克斯\N{\rEnglish}And so, with brida, I fled to wessex.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.52,0:00:42.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}去投奔阿尔弗雷德，他后来成为了国王\N{\rEnglish}To Alfred, a man who would become king.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.84,0:00:47.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}尽管并非所有人都认可  - 我才是父亲的继承人\N{\rEnglish}Though not all agreed. - I am my father's heir.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.28,0:00:50.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我向这位国王宣誓效忠\N{\rEnglish}I swore an oath to this king.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.48,0:00:53.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这份誓言让我失去了布丽达，也让我无法\N{\rEnglish}An oath that lost me brida and prevented me
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.12,0:00:55.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}去投奔我的兄弟拉格纳\N{\rEnglish}from joining my brother ragnar.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.00,0:01:00.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但命运主宰一切\N{\rEnglish}But destiny is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.76,0:01:52.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你不配成婚\N{\rEnglish}You don't deserve to marry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.92,0:01:57.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那位女士是名门闺秀，你不过是个异教徒\N{\rEnglish}That woman is a lady and you're a heathen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.56,0:02:00.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你就算泡一整天澡，身上还是臭\N{\rEnglish}You could bathe all day, you'd still stink.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.40,0:02:05.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你一直盯着我看，小奥达？难不成你想让我娶你？\N{\rEnglish}Have you been watching me, odda the boy? Should I be marrying you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.40,0:02:07.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}给你十枚银币，让你离开这里怎么样\N{\rEnglish}Ten pieces of silver for you to walk away.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.04,0:02:09.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你父亲知道你在这儿吗？\N{\rEnglish}Does your father know you're here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.40,0:02:11.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}十一枚\N{\rEnglish}Eleven pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.40,0:02:19.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不如用我这把剑等重的银子来换？\N{\rEnglish}How about my sword's weight in silver?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.12,0:02:22.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}胡说八道\N{\rEnglish}Nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.84,0:02:27.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那我就娶那姑娘，今晚我还会和她做爱\N{\rEnglish}Then I'll marry the girl. And tonight, I'll plough her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.52,0:02:33.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 你为何要这样说她? - 也许你想把她据为己有\N{\rEnglish}- Why must you talk of her like that? - Perhaps you'd like her for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.40,0:02:36.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你自己想占有她, 是不是?\N{\rEnglish}You want her beneath you. Am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.84,0:02:38.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你这人根本没法讲道理\N{\rEnglish}You're impossible to reason with.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.96,0:02:40.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}什么事在你眼里都是游戏\N{\rEnglish}Everything is a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.04,0:02:45.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}看在米尔德丝的份上, 我希望你在这儿待的时间不会太久\N{\rEnglish}I hope for mildrith's sake, your time on this earth is short.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.76,0:02:47.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你不是郡长\N{\rEnglish}You are not an ealdorman
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.64,0:02:49.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}永远也当不了\N{\rEnglish}and never shall be.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.16,0:02:59.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}嘿! 这边!\N{\rEnglish}Hey! Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.64,0:03:13.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我没被允许去见她, 我还没见过她\N{\rEnglish}I wasn't allowed to meet her. I haven't seen her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.72,0:03:15.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}规矩就是这样\N{\rEnglish}It is the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.48,0:03:19.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}直到昨天我才知道她的存在\N{\rEnglish}I was unaware of her existence till yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.48,0:03:22.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 她是不是又朴素又虔诚? - 虔诚是肯定的\N{\rEnglish}- She'll be plain and pious? - Oh, she'll be pious, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.04,0:03:26.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}要是她是个荡妇, 阿尔弗雷德早就扑上去了\N{\rEnglish}If she was a leg-spreader, Alfred would have been on her by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.60,0:03:28.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你见过她?\N{\rEnglish}Have you seen her?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.44,0:03:30.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}远远看了一眼\N{\rEnglish}A distance away.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.52,0:03:32.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}"朴素"这个词倒是贴切\N{\rEnglish}"Plain" is a fair description.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.40,0:03:34.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}聘礼给了多少?\N{\rEnglish}How much was the bride price?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.12,0:03:36.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}三十三枚\N{\rEnglish}Thirty-three pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.82,0:03:38.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我得支付给她的教父奥达\N{\rEnglish}Which  I've  paid,  to  her  Godfather  Odda,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.12,0:03:41.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我也会确保她收到这笔钱\N{\rEnglish}and which I'll make sure she receives.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.44,0:03:45.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我许下过承诺\N{\rEnglish}I've made promises.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.84,0:03:48.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}复仇之类的\N{\rEnglish}Revenge and such.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.52,0:03:51.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你知道你为什么在这里吗?\N{\rEnglish}Why are you here? Do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.60,0:03:53.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}她给我带来了土地\N{\rEnglish}She brings land.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.56,0:03:57.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我会成为阿尔弗雷德麾下的领主, 能积累财富, 聚拢人马\N{\rEnglish}I'll become a lord under Alfred. I'll be able to make wealth, gather men.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.20,0:04:01.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 夺回属于我的东西    - 这些理由已经足够了\N{\rEnglish}- Take back what's mine. - All reasons enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.48,0:04:04.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}朴素不朴素不重要, 她能派上用场就行\N{\rEnglish}Plain or not, she serves her purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.72,0:04:07.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你许下的承诺必须兑现\N{\rEnglish}The promises you have made will stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.44,0:04:09.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}血仇可以追一辈子\N{\rEnglish}Blood feuds last a lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.40,0:04:14.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你要做的, 浑球, 就是一天一天地活下去, 直到最后一天\N{\rEnglish}What you do, arseling, is you keep living each day until the last.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.92,0:04:21.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}神父终于来了, 咱们赶紧把事儿办了\N{\rEnglish}The priest has arrived finally. Let's get this done.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.84,0:04:24.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你不必做这件事\N{\rEnglish}You do not need to "get this done."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.92,0:04:27.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我会去向阿尔弗雷德求情\N{\rEnglish}I will make a plea to Alfred.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.76,0:04:36.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}她来了, 感谢主\N{\rEnglish}She's here, praise god.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.32,0:04:39.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你站直了, 看起来正经一点, 哪怕人不是很干净\N{\rEnglish}You should stand and look respectful, if not entirely clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.96,0:04:42.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 她看起来怎么样?    - 我猜是吓坏了\N{\rEnglish}- How does she look? - Terrified, I bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.48,0:04:54.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}贝奥卡神父, 能不能把仪式简短一点\N{\rEnglish}If you could be brief with the ceremony, father beocca,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.56,0:04:57.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我会很感激的, 我还有事要见国王\N{\rEnglish}I'd be grateful. I have business with the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.64,0:05:01.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}新娘已经收到聘礼了吗?\N{\rEnglish}The bride has been given her price?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.68,0:05:03.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}她会的\N{\rEnglish}She will.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.00,0:05:08.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你来作见证\N{\rEnglish}You are witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.00,0:05:10.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}谢谢你, 大人\N{\rEnglish}Thank you, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.76,0:05:15.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}若两位新人愿意到祭坛前来...\N{\rEnglish}If the betrothed couple would like to join me at the altar...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.60,0:05:20.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 双手相握  - 快点\N{\rEnglish}- And join hands. - Be brief.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.28,0:05:44.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}愿天上的主垂目怜悯\N{\rEnglish}May god in his heaven look down with mercy
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.68,0:05:48.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他的虔诚仆人乌特雷德与米尔德丝\N{\rEnglish}upon his devoted servants, uhtred and mildrith.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.16,0:05:51.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}愿主赐福这对夫妇, 以爱、子嗣与财富\N{\rEnglish}May he bless their union with love, and children, and wealth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.32,0:05:56.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}也愿他们时刻感恩颂赞\N{\rEnglish}And may they, in turn, be sure to give thanks and praise,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.40,0:06:00.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}每日依照主的圣言而活, 阿门\N{\rEnglish}and live each day according to his holy word. Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.12,0:06:03.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 阿门  - 阿门\N{\rEnglish}- Amen. - Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.16,0:06:07.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你们在天主的见证下，已结为夫妻\N{\rEnglish}You are now joined as man and wife in the eyes of god.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.08,0:06:15.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}喜悦的泪水\N{\rEnglish}Tears of joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.04,0:06:35.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}让我来帮你\N{\rEnglish}Allow me to help you with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.32,0:06:39.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}谢谢你，大人\N{\rEnglish}Thank you, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.36,0:06:43.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我是个幸运的人...\N{\rEnglish}I'm a lucky man...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.12,0:06:46.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}能娶到如此美丽的妻子\N{\rEnglish}To have such a beautiful wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.16,0:06:50.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}追求你的人一定不少吧\N{\rEnglish}There must have been many suitors, I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.60,0:06:52.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你太抬举我了\N{\rEnglish}You're kind to believe so.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.80,0:06:54.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我说得对吗?\N{\rEnglish}Am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.92,0:06:57.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}没有合适的，大人\N{\rEnglish}None suitable, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.76,0:07:00.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我叫乌特雷德，叫我乌特雷德就行\N{\rEnglish}My name's uhtred. Call me uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.28,0:07:03.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}浑球，该上路了\N{\rEnglish}Arseling, time we were on our way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.48,0:07:07.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}或者，你有时候也可以叫我"浑球"\N{\rEnglish}Or from time to time, you may wish to call me "arseling."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.52,0:07:18.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人\N{\rEnglish}Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.36,0:07:22.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}丹麦人\N{\rEnglish}Danes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.24,0:07:25.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们为什么停下来?\N{\rEnglish}Why are we stopping?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.04,0:07:28.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他们是什么人?\N{\rEnglish}Who are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.92,0:07:31.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}多半是强盗\N{\rEnglish}Foragers, most likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.64,0:07:34.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 但终归是丹麦人       - 他们会动手吗?\N{\rEnglish}- But Danes all the same. - Will they attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.40,0:07:36.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}继续走\N{\rEnglish}We walk on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.84,0:07:43.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他们跟上来了\N{\rEnglish}They're following us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.48,0:07:45.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}继续走，他们不会动手的\N{\rEnglish}We walk on. They won't attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.84,0:07:50.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那你为什么拔剑了?\N{\rEnglish} Then why have you drawn your sword?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.28,0:07:53.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}让他们知道，至少有一个人会死在这里\N{\rEnglish}To show them at least one of them will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.44,0:07:55.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}一个，或者两个\N{\rEnglish}One or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.24,0:08:01.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 强盗们已经深入威塞克斯了   - 那是古思伦的人\N{\rEnglish}- Foragers are deep into wessex. - They're guthrum's men.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.76,0:08:04.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他们离伦敦有点远\N{\rEnglish}They're a long way from lundene.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.56,0:08:14.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人, 婚礼已经举行了\N{\rEnglish}Lord, the marriage has taken place.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.28,0:08:16.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他们现在正在去农庄的路上\N{\rEnglish}They are now on the road to the farmstead.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.80,0:08:19.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}好消息, 谢谢你, 奥达\N{\rEnglish}Good news. Thank you, odda.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.56,0:08:22.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}现在看看他如何应对这个挑战\N{\rEnglish}We shall see how he responds to the challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.84,0:08:27.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}婚事已成, 大人, 我确实担心米尔德丝\N{\rEnglish}Now it is done, lord, I do fear for mildrith.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.96,0:08:30.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}她得亲口告诉他实情\N{\rEnglish}She will have to give him the facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.76,0:08:34.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他肯定要冲她发火, 奥达, 这我明白\N{\rEnglish}Oh, he will bark at her, odda, I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.76,0:08:38.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但他真正的怒火, 是留给你我的\N{\rEnglish}But his real anger will be reserved for you and I.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.28,0:08:40.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他不会甘心受天主与国王双重约束\N{\rEnglish}He will not like being beholden to god and to king.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.08,0:08:43.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但若他想成为一个真正的郡长\N{\rEnglish}But if he is to become a true ealdorman,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.12,0:08:47.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}就必须承担这份重担, 这是对他的考验\N{\rEnglish}he must accept his burden. That is the test.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.88,0:08:49.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是, 大人\N{\rEnglish}Yes, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.32,0:08:55.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}米尔德丝是赐给他的美丽慰藉\N{\rEnglish}Mildrith is his beautiful consolation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.92,0:09:01.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他对她动心了吗?\N{\rEnglish}Was he struck by her?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.76,0:09:05.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}动心了, 大人\N{\rEnglish}He was, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.72,0:09:17.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你怎么还没成家?\N{\rEnglish}Why are you not already married?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.84,0:09:21.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你这年纪, 早该有两三个孩子了\N{\rEnglish}You're old enough to have had two or three children by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.44,0:09:23.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}浑球大人\N{\rEnglish}Lord arseling.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.36,0:09:26.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}问这话的时机早过了\N{\rEnglish}There is a time for such questions, and it has past.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.32,0:09:28.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}阿尔弗雷德为何赐我这样一位美丽的新娘?\N{\rEnglish}Why has Alfred gifted me such a beautiful bride?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.08,0:09:35.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我猜是因为欠别人债吧\N{\rEnglish}Has a debt, I'm guessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.36,0:09:37.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这不是我该说的\N{\rEnglish}It's not my place to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.48,0:09:42.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}多少?\N{\rEnglish}How much?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.84,0:09:46.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我父亲想在天主面前得蒙恩宠\N{\rEnglish}My father wanted to find favour with god
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.88,0:09:49.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}所以他把十分之一的土地献给了教会\N{\rEnglish}so he devoted a tenth of his land to the church.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.04,0:09:53.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}教会不拥有这片地, 但有权收取它的出产\N{\rEnglish}They do not own it, but they are entitled to its yield.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.84,0:09:56.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}实际上他们要求收取出产\N{\rEnglish}Indeed, they demand its yield,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.08,0:09:59.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}就算庄稼欠收、丹麦人来袭也不例外\N{\rEnglish}even when crops fail and Danes raid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.88,0:10:01.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}天主是善的\N{\rEnglish}God is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.40,0:10:03.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}于是主教把我父亲告上了法庭\N{\rEnglish}So the bishop took my father to law.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.56,0:10:06.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}债务有多少?\N{\rEnglish}How much is the debt?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.40,0:10:08.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}教会就是法律\N{\rEnglish}The church is the law.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.40,0:10:11.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}法律裁定我父亲欠了他们一大笔钱\N{\rEnglish}And the law decreed that my father owed to them a huge sum.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.64,0:10:14.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 根本超出了他的还款能力        - 多少钱?\N{\rEnglish}- Quite beyond his ability to pay. - How much?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.96,0:10:18.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他不久后就去世了\N{\rEnglish}He died soon after.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.04,0:10:25.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是一笔相当大的数目, 大人\N{\rEnglish}It is a substantial amount, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.16,0:10:27.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}而且每年都在增加\N{\rEnglish}It increases yearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.76,0:10:30.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}阿尔弗雷德本可以免除这笔债, 但他选择不这么做\N{\rEnglish}Alfred could remove the debt. He has chosen not to.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.24,0:10:33.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}欠款共计两千先令, 大人\N{\rEnglish}The amount owed is 2,000 shillings, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.92,0:10:37.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}该死的阿尔弗雷德\N{\rEnglish}Damn him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.16,0:10:41.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他所坚守的一切都该死\N{\rEnglish}Damn everything he stands for.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.32,0:10:44.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 该死的他的教会和他的天主     - 大人, 我不喜欢你说这种亵渎的话\N{\rEnglish}- Damn his church and his god. - Lord, I don't like your blasphemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.04,0:10:46.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我的名字是乌特雷德!\N{\rEnglish}My name is uhtred!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.04,0:10:58.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不过我那么晚才看清这一切，叫我"浑球"也行\N{\rEnglish}Though by all means, call me "arseling" for not seeing this sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.80,0:11:16.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你的新家\N{\rEnglish}Your new home.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.56,0:11:19.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}土地不错, 房子需要修缮\N{\rEnglish}The land is good. The buildings need repair.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.60,0:11:22.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}住在这片地上的几户人家过来向我们道喜\N{\rEnglish}Families who live on the land come to wish us well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.60,0:11:24.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}让他们回自己家去\N{\rEnglish}Send them back to their homes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.88,0:11:29.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他们是来给我们送祝福的, 我认识他们一辈子了\N{\rEnglish}They've come to wish us well. I have known them my whole life.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.96,0:11:32.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人, 夫人\N{\rEnglish}Lord. Lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.56,0:11:35.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}奥斯瓦尔德管着这片农庄, 就住在附近\N{\rEnglish}Oswald manages the farmstead. He lives nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.76,0:11:39.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}欢迎回家, 也请接受我们对你们婚事的美好祝愿\N{\rEnglish}Welcome home. And may we offer our good wishes on your marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.72,0:11:41.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}谢谢你, 奥斯瓦尔德, 谢谢你们\N{\rEnglish}Thank you, oswald. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.12,0:11:46.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你们大家特地聚在这里迎接我和我的主君乌特雷德大人, 真是太好了\N{\rEnglish}And how kind of you all to gather to greet me and my lord uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.16,0:11:49.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人, 我们已经备好了桌席, 请您享用\N{\rEnglish}We have prepared a table, lord, for your pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.40,0:11:53.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}谢谢你们的心意, 不过我们累了\N{\rEnglish}You have my thanks, but we're tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.96,0:11:55.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}明白, 大人\N{\rEnglish}Of course, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.40,0:12:00.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}谢谢你, 奥斯瓦尔德, 你真好\N{\rEnglish}Thank you, oswald. You're kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.84,0:12:04.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我为每家准备了一份婚礼礼物\N{\rEnglish}I have a wedding gift for each family.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.00,0:12:07.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 是银子       - 谢谢您, 米尔德丝夫人\N{\rEnglish}- It is silver. - Thank you, lady mildrith.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.56,0:12:11.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 感谢你们的善意与忠诚         - 真的太感谢了\N{\rEnglish}- For your kindness and your loyalty. - Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.16,0:12:13.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}感谢你们在我不在时替我照看这片土地\N{\rEnglish}For taking care of the land in my absence.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.64,0:12:21.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}哦, 这景象看着真顺眼\N{\rEnglish}Now, there's a welcome sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.96,0:12:31.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我本以为这里会有一座大厅, 结果就看到这个\N{\rEnglish}I was expecting there to be a hall, and I find this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.80,0:12:35.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}把债还清了, 你就能建大厅\N{\rEnglish}Pay off your debts, and you can build a hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.20,0:12:39.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我没说错吧, 那混蛋很精明的——阿尔弗雷德\N{\rEnglish}Didn't I tell you the bastard thinks? Alfred.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.52,0:12:43.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他要是以为能让我低头求他, 那他想得美\N{\rEnglish}If he believes he can make me beg, he can think again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.40,0:12:48.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他不是要你低头, 他要的是你服从\N{\rEnglish}He doesn't want you to beg. He wants you to obey.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.64,0:12:50.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}绝无可能\N{\rEnglish}Never.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.92,0:12:53.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人, 如果您不需要我了, 我去歇着了\N{\rEnglish}If you have need for me, lord, I'll be resting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.52,0:12:55.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我确实累了\N{\rEnglish}It seems I am tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.56,0:13:00.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我欠教会两千先令的债，你倒把银子分给你的佃户\N{\rEnglish}I'm 2,000 shillings in debt to the church, and you hand out silver to your tenants.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.72,0:13:02.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那是我的银子\N{\rEnglish}It is my silver.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.60,0:13:06.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 你可以拿走我钱袋里的钱      - 我不要你钱袋里的钱\N{\rEnglish}- Have what's in my purse. - I don't want what's in your purse.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.08,0:13:08.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那你为何要骂我?\N{\rEnglish}Then why scold me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.04,0:13:16.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那个白胖子, 你庄子上的管事\N{\rEnglish}The stoat. Your farmstead master.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.40,0:13:18.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 奥斯瓦尔德   - 得盯紧他\N{\rEnglish}- Oswald. - He'll need to be watched.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.88,0:13:22.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 他是我父亲信任的人   - 他活得太滋润了\N{\rEnglish}- He was trusted by my father. - He lives too well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.20,0:13:26.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我正要去谷仓     - 你可以睡在屋里\N{\rEnglish}- I'm on my way to the barn. - You can sleep in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.00,0:13:29.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我更喜欢谷仓, 谢谢\N{\rEnglish}I prefer the barn. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.96,0:13:31.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}今晚可是你们的新婚之夜\N{\rEnglish}It is your wedding night.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.24,0:13:33.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}夫人, 晚安\N{\rEnglish}Good night, lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.24,0:13:35.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}浑球\N{\rEnglish}Arseling.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.36,0:13:46.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我可以走了吗?\N{\rEnglish}May I leave now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.76,0:13:50.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你收了多少银子作为聘礼?\N{\rEnglish}How many pieces of silver did you receive as your price?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.12,0:13:52.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}十八块\N{\rEnglish}Eighteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.24,0:13:55.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这数目对吗?\N{\rEnglish}Is that correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.64,0:13:59.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 聘礼是三十三块    - 我相信这只是个疏失\N{\rEnglish}- The price was 33. - I'm sure it was an honest mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.76,0:14:02.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你被骗了\N{\rEnglish}You were robbed,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.96,0:14:04.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}就像我也被骗了一样\N{\rEnglish}as I was robbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.28,0:14:08.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那笔钱是你的保障, 你会拿到全部, 一分不少\N{\rEnglish}That price is your security, and you will have it, all of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.04,0:14:12.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我可以去歇息了吗?\N{\rEnglish}May I rest?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.72,0:14:21.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人, 很抱歉今天让您失望了\N{\rEnglish}I'm sorry the day has been a disappointment for you, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.36,0:15:21.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你心地很好\N{\rEnglish}You have a good heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.20,0:15:24.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}还把自己的银子送出去\N{\rEnglish}Gifting your silver.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.76,0:15:30.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}奥达还欠你十五块, 我会让他补上\N{\rEnglish}Odda owes you 15 pieces more. I'll see that he pays.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.28,0:15:33.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这笔债务不是你的过错, 我不怪你\N{\rEnglish}And the debt's not something I blame you for.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.00,0:15:39.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}阿尔弗雷德欺骗了我, 我当初该更谨慎的\N{\rEnglish}It's Alfred's deceit. I should have been wiser.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.08,0:15:44.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}只是你让我迷了眼\N{\rEnglish}Though I was blinded by you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.84,0:15:55.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你该吃点东西\N{\rEnglish}You should eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.32,0:15:59.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我也该吃点，但我不想一个人吃\N{\rEnglish}I should eat. But I don't want to eat alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.20,0:16:04.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}天主让我成为你的妻子\N{\rEnglish}God has made me your wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.68,0:16:06.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这其中必有缘由\N{\rEnglish}There must be a reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.20,0:16:08.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}天主是慈善的\N{\rEnglish}God is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.48,0:17:09.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你在看什么\N{\rEnglish}What is it you're looking at?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.68,0:17:20.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那片土地上有一道伤痕\N{\rEnglish}There's a scar across the land there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.40,0:17:25.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是丹麦人的行军长龙，没有尽头\N{\rEnglish}The never-ending line of Danes on the march.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.00,0:17:28.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}拉格纳\N{\rEnglish}Ragnar.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.60,0:17:36.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}等消息传到阿尔弗雷德那里，早就来不及了\N{\rEnglish}By the time word reaches Alfred, it would be too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.04,0:17:39.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}除非他们长了翅膀\N{\rEnglish}They would need wings.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.80,0:17:49.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}奥斯瓦尔德，那个方向是什么城镇\N{\rEnglish}Oswald, what town lays in that direction?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.56,0:17:51.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}如果他们继续往西走，一两天后\N{\rEnglish}If they keep going west, in a day or so,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.80,0:17:54.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}就会到达沃勒姆的要塞\N{\rEnglish}they'll come to the fortress at wareham.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.20,0:17:59.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}带上你的家人和其他人躲进山里，等他们过去，快去\N{\rEnglish}Take your family and the others to the hills till they've passed. Do it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.48,0:18:02.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 米尔德丝夫人呢？ - 她跟我一起走...\N{\rEnglish}- And the lady mildrith? - She travels with me...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.24,0:18:04.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}去温彻斯特\N{\rEnglish}To Winchester.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.72,0:18:07.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是，大人\N{\rEnglish}Yes, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.00,0:18:13.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你看到多少人\N{\rEnglish}How many do you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.12,0:18:16.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}问题是，还会有多少人跟来\N{\rEnglish}The question is, how many will follow?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.64,0:18:25.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}威塞克斯正在遭到入侵，而我们却被告知等着，等他祈完祷\N{\rEnglish}Wessex is being invaded and we're told to wait while he prays.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.12,0:18:27.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}天主是他的力量，乌特雷德\N{\rEnglish}God is his strength, uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.12,0:18:30.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他现在该上马冲阵，不是跪在地上祈祷\N{\rEnglish}He needs to be on horseback, not on his knees.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.32,0:18:36.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我讨厌这个地方   - 越来越糟了\N{\rEnglish}- I hate this place. - It grows worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.56,0:18:43.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}没人告诉我你在这里, 真叫人高兴\N{\rEnglish}I was not told you were here. How pleasing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.04,0:18:46.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 大人    - 没想到你不是一个人（怀孕了）\N{\rEnglish}- Lord. - And so much of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.68,0:18:48.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他准备好了吗?\N{\rEnglish}Is he ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.32,0:18:50.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}国王已准备就绪, 贤人会议也是\N{\rEnglish}The king is ready, as is his council.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.72,0:19:05.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你眼睁睁看着三百多个丹麦人大摇大摆地穿越威塞克斯\N{\rEnglish}You watched 300 men or more march clean across wessex
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.48,0:19:07.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}却什么都没做?\N{\rEnglish}and you did nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.52,0:19:09.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我来这里了\N{\rEnglish}I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.56,0:19:12.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}派个信使来就够了\N{\rEnglish}A messenger could have been sent in your place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.16,0:19:14.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 一个小孩都行    - 你为何不和这些丹麦人对峙?\N{\rEnglish}- A boy. - Why did you not confront these Danes?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.80,0:19:17.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你手下有兵, 你的职责就是培养战士\N{\rEnglish}You have men. That's your purpose, to create warriors.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.76,0:19:20.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我只有二十个士兵和他们的妻子, 大多数还在种地\N{\rEnglish}I've been given 20 men and wives, most work the fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.56,0:19:21.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}和丹麦人作战就是送死，大人\N{\rEnglish}It would've been a slaughter, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.04,0:19:23.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但你选择了不战\N{\rEnglish}But you chose not to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.56,0:19:24.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们也没法知道结果了\N{\rEnglish}We'll never know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.08,0:19:27.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}战士只能死一次, 为何要白白送命?\N{\rEnglish}A warrior can only die once. Why die in vain?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.96,0:19:31.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这些丹麦人是从伦敦或东盎格利亚过来的\N{\rEnglish}The Danes have travelled from either lundene or east anglia.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.24,0:19:32.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}难道没有人盯着他们?\N{\rEnglish}Were they not being watched?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.88,0:19:36.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们一直在监视停在泰晤士河上的船, 这是个失误\N{\rEnglish}We have been watching the ships which remain on the tames. A mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.96,0:19:38.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}沃勒姆一旦被占, 战船就会接踵而来\N{\rEnglish}If wareham is captured, ships will follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.96,0:19:41.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}三百人会变成三千人\N{\rEnglish}Three hundred men will become 3,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.60,0:19:45.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我的建议是立刻出兵    - 国王没有向你讨教\N{\rEnglish}- My advice is we march without delay. - I don't recall the king seeking advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.04,0:19:47.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你亲眼看到了多少丹麦人?\N{\rEnglish}How many Danes did you witness?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.56,0:19:51.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}远不止两百, 而且个个都是战士\N{\rEnglish}More than 200 by far. Warriors to a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.04,0:19:55.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}沃勒姆恐怕挡不住他们\N{\rEnglish}Wareham will struggle to hold them back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.56,0:19:57.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}和平就此终结\N{\rEnglish}The peace is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.80,0:20:00.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们别无选择, 只能率兵前往沃勒姆\N{\rEnglish}We have no choice but to march on wareham
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.08,0:20:03.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}祈求天主保佑我们在城堡陷落前赶到\N{\rEnglish}and pray god we arrive before the fortress falls.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.92,0:20:06.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人, 您认为这是一次大规模入侵?\N{\rEnglish}You believe it is an invasion, lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.20,0:20:09.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}很可能是丹麦大军的先兆, 没错\N{\rEnglish}It could well be the beginning of a great Dane army, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.80,0:20:12.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}会议到此结束, 威塞克斯各位郡长, 整备兵马\N{\rEnglish}Council is over. Ealdormen of wessex, prepare your men.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.24,0:20:16.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}贝奥卡神父, 出发前我要做祈祷\N{\rEnglish}Father beocca, I shall pray before we leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.32,0:20:18.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是, 大人\N{\rEnglish}Yes, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.20,0:20:22.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}神父, 我想私下觐见国王\N{\rEnglish}Father, I wish to speak to the king privately.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.92,0:20:24.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我去通禀\N{\rEnglish}I will ask,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.48,0:20:27.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但要我说, 你还得好好学学规矩\N{\rEnglish}but I note that you are still to learn respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.48,0:20:34.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}奥达郡长, 如果我可以说几句\N{\rEnglish}Ealdorman odda, if I may speak out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.04,0:20:38.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你还欠我妻子一半的聘礼\N{\rEnglish}You owe my wife half of her bride-price.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.56,0:20:41.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我付了三十三块银子, 她只收到十八块\N{\rEnglish}I paid 33 pieces of silver. She received only 18.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.12,0:20:44.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}她说这是个无心之失\N{\rEnglish}An honest mistake, she assures me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.08,0:20:49.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是这样吗?\N{\rEnglish}Is this true?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.24,0:20:55.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}把钱补上\N{\rEnglish}Pay him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.84,0:21:02.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}整备人马, 向沃勒姆进发\N{\rEnglish}Ready the men to march on wareham.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.88,0:21:07.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你知道吗, 和米尔德丝做爱很愉快\N{\rEnglish}You should know mildrith is a joy to plough.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.16,0:21:10.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你就是个异教徒\N{\rEnglish}You're a heathen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.44,0:21:12.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}而你是个处男\N{\rEnglish}And you're a virgin.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.84,0:21:15.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我才不是\N{\rEnglish}No, I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.84,0:21:21.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他就是\N{\rEnglish}Yes, he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.04,0:21:48.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}怎么了?\N{\rEnglish}What is it? Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.40,0:21:51.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}答应我, 你一定要平安回来\N{\rEnglish}Promise me you will come back safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.00,0:21:53.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}两条胳膊, 两只耳朵, 一个都不少\N{\rEnglish}Two arms, both ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.88,0:21:55.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}答应我\N{\rEnglish}Promise me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.96,0:21:58.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我会尽力的\N{\rEnglish}I‘ll do my best.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.08,0:22:02.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但你也得答应我同样的事\N{\rEnglish}But only if you do the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.56,0:22:07.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}如果他们来了, 别躲在教堂或修道院里, 去山上, 去林子里\N{\rEnglish}If they come, don't shelter in a church or nunnery. Go to the hills, the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.48,0:22:09.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我会来的\N{\rEnglish}I'll come.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.92,0:22:13.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}为了你们两个\N{\rEnglish}For both of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.68,0:22:16.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}浑球\N{\rEnglish}Arseling.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.36,0:22:18.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}亲她一下, 咱们该走了\N{\rEnglish}Kiss her and let's be on our way.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.36,0:23:36.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}米尔德丝, 亲爱的, 我们一直在找你\N{\rEnglish}Mildrith, my dear, we've been looking for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.56,0:23:40.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}埃尔斯威斯夫人, 见到你真好, 看你这气色, 真是好极了\N{\rEnglish}My lady aelswith. How good to see you, and to see you looking as you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.72,0:23:42.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这孩子就是不肯老实待着\N{\rEnglish}It refuses to keep still.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.64,0:23:45.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我这个也一样    - 唉, 咱们受的这罪\N{\rEnglish}- Mine is the same. - Oh, how we suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.44,0:23:47.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}愿主保佑我们都能平安\N{\rEnglish}I pray we both survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.72,0:23:49.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}愿主保佑我们四个都能平安\N{\rEnglish}I pray we four survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.40,0:23:50.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}天主会说了算的\N{\rEnglish}God will decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.56,0:23:56.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我好想你, 米尔德丝, 每天都为你祈祷\N{\rEnglish}I've missed you, mildrith, and I prayed for you each day.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.20,0:23:58.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 可怜的孩子  - 可怜什么?\N{\rEnglish}- Poor thing. - Why poor?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.20,0:24:02.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}跟那个强塞给你的男人住在一起, 一个异教徒\N{\rEnglish}Living with the man they foisted onto you, the pagan.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.32,0:24:06.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}还得承受他的那些事\N{\rEnglish}Having to take his seed and the like.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.24,0:24:09.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}乌特雷德是个好人, 他待我很好\N{\rEnglish}Uhtred is decent. He treats me well.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.24,0:24:11.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}真的很好\N{\rEnglish}He does.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.96,0:24:14.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}天主会因你的忠诚而赐福于你\N{\rEnglish}God will bless your loyalty.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.80,0:24:19.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但但愿他能很快战死沙场\N{\rEnglish}But with luck, he will fall in battle, and soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.44,0:24:24.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}快告诉我你饿了\N{\rEnglish}Please tell me that you're hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.48,0:24:27.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我有点饿    - 去厨房找我\N{\rEnglish}- I am a little. - Meet me in the kitchens.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.88,0:24:30.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我已经为孕妇备好了一顿饭\N{\rEnglish}I have arranged a meal for the pregnant.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.20,0:24:31.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但别急着祷告\N{\rEnglish}But do not rush prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.88,0:24:34.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不不, 当然不会, 呵\N{\rEnglish}No. No. Of course not. Heh.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.92,0:24:49.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}主啊, 他不是你最谦卑虔诚的仆人\N{\rEnglish}Lord, he is not your most humble or devout servant.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.16,0:24:50.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但我祈求你能...\N{\rEnglish}But I pray...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.56,0:24:53.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}保他平安\N{\rEnglish}Keep him safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.96,0:24:56.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}让他完成你的旨意\N{\rEnglish}Let him do your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.76,0:24:59.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}让他亲眼看见自己的孩子\N{\rEnglish}Let him see his child.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.40,0:25:06.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我很高兴今天见到你的妻子\N{\rEnglish}I was pleased to see your lady today, your wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.20,0:25:09.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}而且她怀着孩子\N{\rEnglish}And carrying a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.72,0:25:12.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这是天主的恩赐\N{\rEnglish}It's god's blessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.44,0:25:15.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}感觉就像昨天的事一样\N{\rEnglish}It seems like only yesterday
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.24,0:25:18.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我先给你施洗, 取名奥斯伯特, 后来又改名乌特雷德\N{\rEnglish}I was baptising you as osbert, and then again as uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.24,0:25:23.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你想和国王谈什么事?\N{\rEnglish}What is it you wish to speak about with the king?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.96,0:25:25.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那是我和国王之间的事\N{\rEnglish}It's between myself and the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.36,0:25:28.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他关注着你, 乌特雷德\N{\rEnglish}He's watching you, uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.46,0:25:30.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 天主？ - 阿尔弗雷德\N{\rEnglish}- God?   - Alfred
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.24,0:25:33.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}看你怎么行事, 以国王的身份评判你\N{\rEnglish}Watching how you behave, judging you as a lord
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.72,0:25:35.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他没有资格评判我\N{\rEnglish}He has no right to judge.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.68,0:25:37.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他是国王\N{\rEnglish}He's a king.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.20,0:25:42.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他在婚事上骗了我\N{\rEnglish}He lied to me regarding the marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.16,0:25:43.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你说的是那笔债吗?\N{\rEnglish}Are you referring to the debt?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.48,0:25:46.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 你知道这件事? - 这不是秘密\N{\rEnglish}- You know of it? - It's not a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.04,0:25:49.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我劝你表现出你已经接受了\N{\rEnglish}And I urge you to show him you accepted,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.76,0:25:52.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}尤其是那笔债是欠教会的\N{\rEnglish}especially as it is owed to the church.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.04,0:25:57.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你必须保持冷静, 乌特雷德, 要懂得敬重\N{\rEnglish}You must remain calm, uhtred, respectful.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.40,0:26:08.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人\N{\rEnglish}My lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.92,0:26:11.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我请求私下... - 你吃过东西了吗?\N{\rEnglish}- I requested a private... - Have you eaten?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.84,0:26:21.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}有时候我很馋肉食...\N{\rEnglish}There are times when I crave meat...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.96,0:26:25.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}以及别的东西\N{\rEnglish}And other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.56,0:26:30.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但我知道那满足感转瞬即逝, 痛苦却会绵延\N{\rEnglish}But I know the gratification would be fleeting, the suffering prolonged,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.92,0:26:32.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}所以我忍着吃粥\N{\rEnglish}and so I suffer gruel.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.76,0:26:36.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不过我夫人不准我叫粥, 非要叫"肉汤"\N{\rEnglish}Though my wife will not allow it to be called anything other than "broth."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.60,0:26:40.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你一定会很高兴得知我的细作带来了消息\N{\rEnglish}You will be happy to learn that my spies have news.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.68,0:26:43.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 来自沃勒姆的? - 来自爱尔兰\N{\rEnglish}- From wareham? - From Ireland.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.40,0:26:47.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}乌巴的兄弟伊瓦尔在那里被杀了, 本来无关紧要\N{\rEnglish}Ivar, brother of ubba, has been killed there, which would be irrelevant,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.36,0:26:50.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但乌巴要亲自为他复仇\N{\rEnglish}but for the fact ubba wishes to avenge him personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.60,0:26:52.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这是真的?\N{\rEnglish}This is true?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.52,0:26:58.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}海那边一个爱尔兰人杀了个丹麦人, 天下就此变局\N{\rEnglish}An irishman across the sea kills a Dane, and the world changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.16,0:27:01.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这是天主的旨意\N{\rEnglish}The hand of god.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.88,0:27:06.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}乌巴会这么做吗? 就这么抛下古思伦?\N{\rEnglish}Is this something ubba would do? Abandon guthrum?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.04,0:27:11.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}为了替兄弟报仇, 会的, 只要他的巫师那边说得通\N{\rEnglish}To avenge his brother, yes. If guided by his sorcerer's story.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.56,0:27:14.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他还有个巫师?\N{\rEnglish}He has a sorcerer?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.80,0:27:18.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这巫师是做什么的?\N{\rEnglish}And what does this sorcerer do?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.68,0:27:20.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}施法? 行巫术?\N{\rEnglish}Cast spells? Perform magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.84,0:27:22.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他出谋划策, 大人\N{\rEnglish}He advises, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.32,0:27:24.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他寻找征兆\N{\rEnglish}He looks for omens.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.36,0:27:28.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 吉兆凶兆都看    - 哦, 简直是无稽之谈\N{\rEnglish}- Signs, good and bad. - Oh, what nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.28,0:27:31.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人, 奇迹若不是魔法, 又是什么?\N{\rEnglish}What are miracles, lord, if not magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.04,0:27:34.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}奇迹是天主所为, 非人力所及\N{\rEnglish}Miracles are performed by god, not man.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.56,0:27:37.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}丹麦人也这么说 他们认为预兆是众神赐予的礼物\N{\rEnglish}Danes say the same. Omens are gifts from gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.16,0:27:38.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他们错了\N{\rEnglish}And they are mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.04,0:27:41.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是谁示意乌巴去爱尔兰的?\N{\rEnglish}Who gave the sign for ubba to go to Ireland?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.52,0:27:44.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 是你们的神还是他们的神? - 只有一个神\N{\rEnglish}- The hand of your god or theirs? - There's one god.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.56,0:27:47.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那他一定也跟丹麦人说过话\N{\rEnglish}Then he must have spoken to the Danes.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.36,0:27:50.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}乌巴如今去了爱尔兰\N{\rEnglish}With ubba now in Ireland,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.84,0:27:54.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}古思伦就得决定他是否要单独迎战了\N{\rEnglish}guthrum must now decide whether he will fight alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.72,0:27:56.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他不会单独出战的\N{\rEnglish}He won't fight alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.00,0:27:58.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不是说他赢不了\N{\rEnglish}Not that he couldn't win.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.92,0:28:01.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他会怕折损太多手下\N{\rEnglish}He will fear losing too many of his men.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.32,0:28:02.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是的, 大人\N{\rEnglish}Yes, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.12,0:28:06.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我明白了一件事...\N{\rEnglish}I am learning...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.20,0:28:09.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这些异教徒只顾自身利益\N{\rEnglish}That the heathen cares only for personal gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.04,0:28:12.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}丹麦人绝对受不了我喝的粥\N{\rEnglish}A Dane could never suffer my gruel.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.08,0:28:15.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}应该是"肉汤", 大人\N{\rEnglish}"Broth," lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.96,0:28:21.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}郡长乌特雷德, 你和米尔德丝过得好吗?\N{\rEnglish}You are happy, ealdorman uhtred, with mildrith?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.76,0:28:25.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}很好, 大人, 她是个好妻子\N{\rEnglish}Yes, lord. She's a good wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.12,0:28:31.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不过要是早知道我得欠两千先令, 我当初绝不会娶她\N{\rEnglish}Though I never would have married her had I known I'd owe 2,000 shillings.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.16,0:28:32.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}而且每年还在涨\N{\rEnglish}Which increases yearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.64,0:28:34.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}您一句话, 这债就能免了\N{\rEnglish}On your word, the debt can be lifted.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.96,0:28:37.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我凭什么让教会少收两千先令?\N{\rEnglish}Why should I deny the church 2,000 shillings?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.44,0:28:40.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我根本不知道还有这债   - 这又不是什么秘密\N{\rEnglish}- I wasn't aware I'd owe it. - It is not a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.16,0:28:45.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}正是牺牲与忏悔, 让我们有别于异教徒\N{\rEnglish}Sacrifice and penance are what separate us from the heathen.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.40,0:28:49.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我有我的肉汤, 你有你的债\N{\rEnglish}I have my broth, you have your debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.84,0:28:54.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}威塞克斯需要一支军队, 你同意吗?\N{\rEnglish}Wessex needs an army, would you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.92,0:28:59.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}一支常设的强大军队\N{\rEnglish}A permanent and formidable army.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.44,0:29:03.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是，大人\N{\rEnglish}Yes, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.84,0:29:08.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}英格兰一旦真正建立起来，就需要一支更强大的军队\N{\rEnglish}England, when it finally emerges, shall need a greater army.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.28,0:29:14.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}驻军将达数千之众，全都需要粮饷\N{\rEnglish}Garrisons of many thousands of men, all will need feeding and payment.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.88,0:29:17.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我打算让所有地主\N{\rEnglish}It is my intention that all landowners shall contribute
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.96,0:29:21.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}共同承担这支军队及其将领的给养\N{\rEnglish}to the feeding of this army and its commanders.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.80,0:29:24.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我还需要将领，乌特雷德\N{\rEnglish}And I will need commanders, uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.36,0:29:29.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}像罗马那些伟大统帅一样的人\N{\rEnglish}Men like the great generals of Rome.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.76,0:29:34.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}把这笔债当作一份馈赠吧\N{\rEnglish}Look upon the debt as a gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.16,0:29:39.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这是你向威塞克斯和英格兰证明忠心的机会\N{\rEnglish}A means of proving your devotion to wessex and to england.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.36,0:29:43.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 要是当初有人告诉我实情……   - 我看你还戴着那枚护身符\N{\rEnglish}- If I'd been told the truth from... - You still wear the amulet, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.96,0:29:46.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}为了铭记拉格纳伯爵\N{\rEnglish}To remind me of Earl ragnar.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.64,0:29:50.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你为何不陪你妻子去教堂？为何不向天主祈祷？\N{\rEnglish}Why do you not attend church with your wife? Why do you not pray to god?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.64,0:29:53.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}天主创造了我身边的一切\N{\rEnglish}God created everything that surrounds me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.96,0:29:57.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}田野、河流、森林，这片大地就是我的教堂\N{\rEnglish}The fields, rivers, the forests. The land is my church.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.88,0:30:01.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我每天都在祈祷，大人……\N{\rEnglish}And I pray each day, lord...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.44,0:30:03.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}默默地祈祷\N{\rEnglish}In silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.76,0:30:22.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他是管不住的\N{\rEnglish}He cannot be tamed.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.00,0:30:25.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但他是可以信任的\N{\rEnglish}But he can be trusted.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.80,0:30:29.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我不会彻底放弃他\N{\rEnglish}I will not abandon him completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.36,0:30:33.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我想他还有用处\N{\rEnglish}He may have a use, I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.60,0:30:47.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}听好了，沃勒姆已经失守\N{\rEnglish}Hear me now. Wareham has fallen.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.68,0:30:49.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们立刻出兵\N{\rEnglish}We march at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.64,0:30:52.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}每个人都要按国王的命令行事\N{\rEnglish}Every man is to be ready to do as the king asks.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.12,0:30:56.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}丹麦人已经攻占了那座要塞\N{\rEnglish}The Danes have taken the fortress.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.32,0:30:58.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}沃勒姆已经陷落 立刻出发\N{\rEnglish}Wareham has fallen. We march at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.72,0:31:02.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}今天结束之前, 我们可能就踩在血水和内脏里了\N{\rEnglish}We could be slipping in blood and entrails before the day is out.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.56,0:31:38.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}别管他 够所有人分的\N{\rEnglish}Leave him. There's enough for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.96,0:31:48.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}古思伦, 他们来了\N{\rEnglish}Guthrum, they're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.72,0:31:51.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}撒克逊大军正在集结\N{\rEnglish}The Saxon army is gathering.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.12,0:31:54.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 是阿尔弗雷德吗? - 是\N{\rEnglish}- Is it Alfred? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.32,0:31:58.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}要塞修缮好了吗, 防守稳固吗?\N{\rEnglish}Is the fortress repaired and secure?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.46,0:32:00.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}很稳固\N{\rEnglish}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.56,0:32:03.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}很好, 他不会进攻\N{\rEnglish}Good. He will not attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.20,0:32:06.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他不需要进攻, 他知道我们几天之内就会断粮\N{\rEnglish}He doesn't need to. He knows we'll be hungry within days.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.88,0:32:08.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我们可以去劫掠  - 不行\N{\rEnglish}- We can raid. - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.36,0:32:12.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他会把周边村子的粮仓清空\N{\rEnglish}He will empty all the grain stores in the surrounding villages.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.56,0:32:22.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我发现这些教堂房间出奇地安静祥和\N{\rEnglish}I have found these church rooms to be strangely quiet and peaceful.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.20,0:32:27.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人, 我带着兵马跋山涉水横穿英格兰, 不是来这儿挨饿的\N{\rEnglish}Lord, I didn't march my men halfway across england for them to starve.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.76,0:32:31.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我去城墙巡查          - 拉格纳, 我们是来打仗的\N{\rEnglish}- I shall be on the ramparts. - We came for war, ragnar.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.08,0:32:34.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但乌巴背信弃义\N{\rEnglish}But ubba has reneged.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.56,0:32:38.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 他是去为兄弟报仇     - 但你在这里\N{\rEnglish}- To avenge his brother. - But you are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.08,0:32:43.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你不该去为你父亲报仇吗?\N{\rEnglish}Should you not be avenging your father?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.16,0:32:46.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 时机未到     - 是啊\N{\rEnglish}- When the time is right. - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.00,0:32:49.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}时机未到\N{\rEnglish}When the time is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.68,0:32:54.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们已经迈出了进攻威塞克斯的第一步\N{\rEnglish}We have taken the first steps against wessex.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.20,0:32:59.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但乌巴的离开让我们实力大损\N{\rEnglish}But ubba has left us weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.56,0:33:02.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他把我们所有人都置于险地\N{\rEnglish}He put all of our lives at risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.60,0:33:05.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}所以在乌巴回来之前\N{\rEnglish}So until ubba returns,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.40,0:33:07.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们必须谈和\N{\rEnglish}we have to make peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.16,0:33:22.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}所以如果你在那里的话...\N{\rEnglish}So if you are there...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.42,0:33:24.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}罗马的天主\N{\rEnglish}God of Rome
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.08,0:33:27.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}来砍死我啊\N{\rEnglish}Strike me down.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.48,0:33:32.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我想也不会\N{\rEnglish}I thought not.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.92,0:33:37.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们来这里, 是要让他们看清楚我们有多少人\N{\rEnglish}We are here to show them how many we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.76,0:33:41.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们来这里, 是要让他们看清楚我们有多少人!\N{\rEnglish}We are here to show them how many we are!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.72,0:33:43.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们有天主同在\N{\rEnglish}That we are here with god.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.00,0:33:45.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这片土地是我们的\N{\rEnglish}And that this is our land.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.68,0:33:47.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们有天主同在!\N{\rEnglish}That we are here with god!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.16,0:33:49.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这片土地是我们的!\N{\rEnglish}And this is our land!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.08,0:33:52.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这是我们的土地!\N{\rEnglish}This is our land!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.12,0:33:55.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们的威塞克斯!\N{\rEnglish}Our wessex!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.88,0:33:57.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这是我们的英格兰!\N{\rEnglish}This is our england!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.08,0:34:03.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}任何敢来抢夺的异教徒杂种, 我们都要杀光他们!\N{\rEnglish}And we shall murder any heathen bastard that tries to take it!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.48,0:34:27.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 他们想谈判, 大人     - 我知道他们想要什么\N{\rEnglish}- They wish to talk, lord. - I know what they want.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.12,0:34:29.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他们想拖时间\N{\rEnglish}They want time.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.04,0:34:33.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}奥达, 带上你的卫兵跟我去, 利奥弗里克, 你也来\N{\rEnglish}Odda, with your guards, you shall go with me. Leofric, you as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.16,0:34:37.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 还有塞尔比克斯神父   - 是, 大人\N{\rEnglish}- And father selbix. - Yes, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.44,0:34:39.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}利奥弗里克，你觉得那座要塞怎么样?\N{\rEnglish}Leofric, What do you make of the fortress?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.64,0:34:41.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}看起来相当坚固, 大人\N{\rEnglish}It looks strong enough, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.64,0:34:46.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}没有缺口, 也没有明显损毁\N{\rEnglish}No breach. No signs of lasting damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.28,0:34:48.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}如果我们强攻呢?\N{\rEnglish}And if we attacked?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.32,0:34:51.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们会损失惨重\N{\rEnglish}We would suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.24,0:34:55.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}能打进去就算走运了, 大人\N{\rEnglish}We'd be lucky to see the inside, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.84,0:34:58.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}早上好, 阿尔弗雷德国王\N{\rEnglish}Good morning, king Alfred.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.72,0:35:00.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}丹麦人古思伦\N{\rEnglish}Guthrum of the Danes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.96,0:35:04.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我现在也是国王了, 东盎格利亚之王\N{\rEnglish}I, too, am a king now, of east anglia.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.60,0:35:06.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不必行礼\N{\rEnglish}You don't need to bow.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.52,0:35:09.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我来开门见山\N{\rEnglish}I will begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.24,0:35:10.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我提议停战\N{\rEnglish}I propose a truce.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.60,0:35:16.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}古思伦伯爵, 要想停战, 你必须再次离开威塞克斯\N{\rEnglish}For any truce to occur, Earl guthrum, you must leave wessex once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.60,0:35:18.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 若我拒绝呢? - 我们便将你团团围困\N{\rEnglish}- And if I refuse? - We surround you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.12,0:35:20.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是啊, 你们围住的不过是一座小堡垒\N{\rEnglish}Yes, you surround a small fortress,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.12,0:35:24.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但我们丹麦人围住的是你整个王国, 话虽如此\N{\rEnglish}but we Danes surround your entire kingdom. That said,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.36,0:35:27.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我已决定从海路撤离\N{\rEnglish}I've decided I shall leave by sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.04,0:35:29.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}因此我要派人去调船\N{\rEnglish}Therefore, I will send for ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.04,0:35:32.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 要多少船? - 不超过十五艘\N{\rEnglish}- How many ships? - No more than 15.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.32,0:35:34.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}好吧\N{\rEnglish}Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.80,0:35:36.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你的船有一个月时间抵达\N{\rEnglish}Your ships have one month to arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.88,0:35:40.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 时间不够    - 只供应一个月的食物和麦酒\N{\rEnglish}- Not enough time. - Food and ale for one month only,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.60,0:35:42.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}否则你就走路滚回东盎格利亚\N{\rEnglish}or you will walk back to east anglia.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.00,0:35:46.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那我就调两百艘船来, 希望在我们饿死之前能到\N{\rEnglish}Then I'll send for 200 ships and hope they arrive before we starve.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.72,0:35:49.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 一个月根本不够      - 这是我的底线\N{\rEnglish}- One month is not enough. - That is my limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.64,0:35:52.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你夺不回这座堡垒, 你心里清楚\N{\rEnglish}You cannot take back the fortress. You know this.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.44,0:35:54.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}食物和麦酒只供应一个月, 不会再多了\N{\rEnglish}Food and ale for one month, no more.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.04,0:35:58.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}到那时候, 海上的风暴也该来了\N{\rEnglish}By which time, the sea storms will have arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.44,0:36:02.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 那是主赐的风暴    - 我们会在一个月内离开\N{\rEnglish}- God's storms. - We will be gone within a month,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.88,0:36:05.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}从食物和麦酒送达之日起算\N{\rEnglish}beginning upon the delivery of food and ale.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.36,0:36:19.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}乌特雷德, 祈祷结束后来见我\N{\rEnglish}Uhtred, you will come to me following prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.72,0:36:22.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 是, 大人\N{\rChinese}- 塞尔比克斯神父, 你陪我一同祈祷\N{\rEnglish}- Yes, lord. - Father selbix, you will pray with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.04,0:36:24.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是, 大人\N{\rEnglish}Yes, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.92,0:36:30.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}请坐\N{\rEnglish}Please sit.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.64,0:36:36.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}多谢, 大人\N{\rEnglish}Thank you, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.68,0:36:41.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我有件事要交给你, 神父\N{\rEnglish}I have a task for you, father.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.24,0:36:44.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人请说\N{\rEnglish}You only have to speak it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.52,0:36:49.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}作为和平的保证, 你将被送去做人质, 一共十人\N{\rEnglish}As a guarantee of the peace, you will be given up as a hostage, one of ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.20,0:36:53.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}丹麦人那边也会交出十人作为交换\N{\rEnglish}The Danes, too, will give ten in exchange.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.32,0:37:01.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人, 异教徒不把神父当回事\N{\rEnglish}Lord, the pagans do not value priests.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.56,0:37:03.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你还不如送头猎犬过去呢\N{\rEnglish}You might just as well offer a hound.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.08,0:37:06.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我听说古思伦对我们的信仰颇感好奇\N{\rEnglish}I hear guthrum is curious about our faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.48,0:37:09.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我希望你去做他的老师\N{\rEnglish}I would like you to become his teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.08,0:37:12.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}给他传道授业\N{\rEnglish}Provide instruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.44,0:37:16.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}要是他不愿意学呢?\N{\rEnglish}And if he refuses to be a student?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.56,0:37:19.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那就坚持下去\N{\rEnglish}Then persist.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.16,0:37:23.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}用你一贯的方式, 温和, 带点幽默\N{\rEnglish}Gently with humour, as is your manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.00,0:37:26.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你要清楚...\N{\rEnglish}Make no mistake...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.04,0:37:32.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}只要古思伦愿意受洗\N{\rEnglish}Should guthrum ever consent to being baptised,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.68,0:37:34.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这场战争就结束了\N{\rEnglish}then this war is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.04,0:37:37.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}英格兰就是我们的了\N{\rEnglish}England is ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.08,0:37:42.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你做的将是真正的天主的事业\N{\rEnglish}This would be truly god's work you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.64,0:37:46.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}恕我直言, 大人\N{\rEnglish}Forgive me, lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.04,0:37:49.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我心里确实害怕\N{\rEnglish}but I cannot help but feel afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.96,0:37:54.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他们对待神父可不只是杀了了事\N{\rEnglish}They are not content to simply kill a priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.68,0:37:59.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}恐惧人人都有\N{\rEnglish}Fear is within all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.48,0:38:02.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}勇气也是\N{\rEnglish}As is strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.32,0:38:35.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人, 等休战破裂, 我上阵杀敌还更有用\N{\rEnglish}Lord, I'd be more useful as a warrior for when the truce fails.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.92,0:38:38.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}休战还能撑一段时间\N{\rEnglish}Oh, the truce will hold for a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.28,0:38:41.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}在此期间, 你将是我安插在那座堡垒里的眼线\N{\rEnglish}And in that time, you will be my eyes and ears inside the fortress.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.04,0:38:44.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 监听什么? - 乌巴的消息\N{\rEnglish}- Listening for what? - For ubba.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.64,0:38:48.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}一旦听说他回来, 你就想办法逃出来\N{\rEnglish}If and when you hear of his return, you will escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.24,0:38:50.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 要是我被锁链拴着呢? - 我们的人会解散\N{\rEnglish}- And if I'm in chains? - Our men shall disband.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.88,0:38:52.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}让他们去种地\N{\rEnglish}There are fields to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.36,0:38:55.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我会在山丘上建一座烽火台, 你逃出来就点火\N{\rEnglish}I'll build a beacon on the hill. You'll escape and light the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.04,0:38:58.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人, 您知道逃跑几乎是不可能的\N{\rEnglish}Lord, you know that escape will be near impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.12,0:39:03.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}乌巴一旦回来, 人质就会被杀, 丹麦人随即会发动进攻\N{\rEnglish}If ubba returns, the hostages will be killed and the Danes will attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.72,0:39:05.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}一看到烽火燃起\N{\rEnglish}Upon sight of this beacon being lit,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.80,0:39:08.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}其他烽火也会相继点燃, 威塞克斯全境都会集结备战\N{\rEnglish}other fires will start. Wessex will be called to arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.76,0:39:12.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 如果我拒绝去做人质呢? - 会有另一个人去点那把火\N{\rEnglish}- If I refuse to become a hostage? - Another man shall light the beacon.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.68,0:39:14.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你为何就是不肯接纳我?\N{\rEnglish}Why can't you accept me?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.48,0:39:17.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我从未说过半句谎话, 为何总要考验我?\N{\rEnglish}I've been nothing but truthful. Why am I always put to the test?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.08,0:39:20.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你为何不给你的国王应有的尊重?\N{\rEnglish}Why do you not show your king respect that is due?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.84,0:39:22.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}因为你, 不管什么地方来的乌特雷德\N{\rEnglish}Because you, uhtred of wherever,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.68,0:39:26.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}根本没把我当你的国王, 也没把我的天主当你的天主\N{\rEnglish}you do not see me as your king. You do not see my god as your god.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.68,0:39:28.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 大人? - 我还没说完\N{\rEnglish}- My lord? - I am not finished with you yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.84,0:39:34.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}古思伦一直在等乌巴从爱尔兰回来的消息\N{\rEnglish}Guthrum is waiting to hear of ubba's return from Ireland.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.96,0:39:39.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我需要尽早得知此事, 越快越好, 而你...\N{\rEnglish}I need to know when this occurs, sooner rather than later. You...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.20,0:39:44.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是唯一有可能最先带回这个消息的人\N{\rEnglish}Are the only man who could possibly provide this information sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.44,0:39:47.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}没错, 你可能会死\N{\rEnglish}Yes, it is possible that you will die,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.80,0:39:51.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但我们大概都难逃一死\N{\rEnglish}but it is likely that we shall all die.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.28,0:39:55.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你要去丹麦人那里\N{\rEnglish}You will go to the Danes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.88,0:39:57.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}以什么身份去, 是撒克逊人质\N{\rEnglish}How you go, as a Saxon hostage
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.00,0:40:00.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}还是维京勇士, 是你的选择\N{\rEnglish}or as a viking warrior, becomes your choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.60,0:40:08.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我会照你说的做\N{\rEnglish}I'll do as you ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.60,0:40:15.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但如果我被扣押期间孩子降生，我请求你给我带个信\N{\rEnglish}But if my child is born while I'm captive, I ask that you send word.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.72,0:40:17.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}当然\N{\rEnglish}Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.68,0:40:22.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}若你死在被扣押期间，放心，你的债也随你一起消了\N{\rEnglish}And should you die as a captive, rest assured, your debt shall die with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.92,0:40:37.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他们会善待我们吗？\N{\rEnglish}Will they treat us well?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.96,0:40:39.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你是他们中的一员\N{\rEnglish}You are one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.88,0:40:43.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我若是他们的一员，为何还要做人质？\N{\rEnglish}If I am one of them, then why am I a hostage?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.52,0:40:47.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}只要停战协议还在，他们就会善待我们\N{\rEnglish}They'll treat us well for as long as the truce holds.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.64,0:40:50.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 若协议破裂呢？- 他们会把我们全杀了，\N{\rEnglish}- If it fails? - They'll kill us all,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.36,0:40:52.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}从神父开始，哈！\N{\rEnglish}starting with the priest. Heh!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.88,0:40:56.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我已坦然接受，我已准备好了\N{\rEnglish}I've made my peace. I am ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.84,0:40:59.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}晚上好，愿主保佑你们\N{\rEnglish}Good evening and god bless you all.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.88,0:41:02.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}可怜的人\N{\rEnglish}Poor wretches.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.56,0:41:04.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那我们呢，神父，我们又算什么？\N{\rEnglish}And us, father, what are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.36,0:41:06.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们是有福之人，大人，我们认识天主\N{\rEnglish}We are fortunate, lord. We know god.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.20,0:41:10.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不过坦白说，我不急着去见他\N{\rEnglish}Although granted, I'm in no hurry to meet him.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.44,0:41:12.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}愿天主也这么想\N{\rEnglish}Let us pray he feels the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.68,0:41:14.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}阿门\N{\rEnglish}Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.64,0:41:43.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}就这群乌合之众，还让那么多人胆寒？\N{\rEnglish}Is this rabble what so many are afraid of?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.28,0:41:45.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}来来来，他们跟孩子没两样\N{\rEnglish}Come. They're like children.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.72,0:41:53.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}够了，够了！\N{\rEnglish}Enough. Enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.20,0:41:57.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他们暂时是我们的客人\N{\rEnglish}They are our guests for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.16,0:42:00.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}只有一条规矩\N{\rEnglish}There's one rule only.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.28,0:42:03.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}天黑之后，\N{\rEnglish}At nightfall,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.24,0:42:05.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}所有人集合，到教堂里睡觉\N{\rEnglish}you will gather and sleep at the church.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.12,0:42:08.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}门会被封死\N{\rEnglish}The doors will be barred.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.88,0:42:15.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}天亮之后, 你们可以自由行走、交谈、跳跃、交欢、携带武器\N{\rEnglish}At daybreak, you will then be free to walk, talk, jump, hump, carry weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.48,0:42:18.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我的人奉命不会杀你们...\N{\rEnglish}My men have orders not to kill you...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.56,0:42:22.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}除非你们该死\N{\rEnglish}Unless you deserve to be killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.64,0:42:28.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我是古思伦\N{\rEnglish}I am guthrum.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.40,0:42:31.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}总有一天, 我将成为你们的国王\N{\rEnglish}And one day, I shall be your king.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.40,0:42:33.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你们听懂我说的了吗?\N{\rEnglish}Do you understand what I have said?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.80,0:42:35.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你们都要说:"是的, 大人"\N{\rEnglish}You will all say, "yes, lord."
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.32,0:42:39.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是的, 大人\N{\rEnglish}Yes, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.24,0:42:41.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我没听见\N{\rEnglish}I did not hear you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.52,0:42:48.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们听懂了, 大人\N{\rEnglish}I understand you, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.16,0:42:51.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}也许我会把你作为礼物送给乌巴\N{\rEnglish}Maybe I will make a present of you to ubba.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.64,0:42:55.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 要是他从爱尔兰回来的话       - 他可能不会回来, 也说不定\N{\rEnglish}- Should he ever return from Ireland. - He may not. That's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.76,0:42:58.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但到那时他的人就会成为我的人\N{\rEnglish}But then his men will become my men,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.28,0:43:01.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我会亲手杀了你, 以此向他致敬\N{\rEnglish}and I will honour him by killing you myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.28,0:43:05.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}也许用箭\N{\rEnglish}With arrows, perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.76,0:43:08.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 拉格纳·拉格纳森    - 在这\N{\rEnglish}- Ragnar ragnarson. - Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.36,0:43:11.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你对这人很熟, 让他别出现在我眼前\N{\rEnglish}You know this one well. Keep him out of my sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.36,0:43:14.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}把他们带去教堂, 给他们吃的\N{\rEnglish}Take them to the church. Feed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.56,0:43:23.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}现在你们到了该待的地方\N{\rEnglish}Now you are where you belong.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.24,0:43:25.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}现在我和我兄弟在一起了\N{\rEnglish}Now I'm with my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.84,0:43:30.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我会让你重新感受身为丹麦人是什么滋味, 让你留下来\N{\rEnglish}I will remind you what it is like to be a Dane and make you stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.84,0:43:32.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}布丽达也在这里\N{\rEnglish}Brida's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.16,0:43:53.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我梦到过你, 小狐狸\N{\rEnglish}I dream about you, Vixen.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.44,0:43:57.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}听到这话我一点都不意外\N{\rEnglish}I'm not surprised to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.80,0:44:00.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你长大了, 哈哈\N{\rEnglish}You've grown up. Heh, heh.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.64,0:44:07.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你该知道我现在跟着拉格纳, 他是我的男人\N{\rEnglish}You should know I'm with ragnar now. He's my man.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.28,0:44:10.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这是好事\N{\rEnglish}That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.44,0:44:14.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这是好事\N{\rEnglish}That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.92,0:44:18.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你也该知道, 我成婚了\N{\rEnglish}You should know that I am married.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.28,0:44:20.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}成婚了?\N{\rEnglish}Married?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.24,0:44:24.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 你真的长大了  - 他成婚了?\N{\rEnglish}- You have grown up. - He's married?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.24,0:44:27.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}对, 他成婚了\N{\rEnglish}Yes, he is married.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.48,0:44:29.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}时间过得比我想的快多了\N{\rEnglish}Time is moving quicker than I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.20,0:44:31.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}今晚, 我们喝个痛快\N{\rEnglish}Tonight, we get drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.40,0:44:33.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}必须的\N{\rEnglish}We must.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.28,0:44:38.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 晚上我得呆在教堂里\N{\rChinese}- 不, 今晚我们喝个痛快\N{\rEnglish}- I need to be inside the church. - No, tonight we get drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.48,0:44:40.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我亲自带你去教堂\N{\rEnglish}I'll take you to the church myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.52,0:44:43.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}或者喝倒在哪儿就睡哪儿, 哈哈\N{\rEnglish}Or we sleep where we fall, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.04,0:44:45.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}还有, 呃...\N{\rEnglish}And, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.24,0:44:48.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们得谈谈将来的事\N{\rEnglish}We must talk of the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.60,0:45:05.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们是桨手!\N{\rEnglish}We are oarsmen!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.20,0:45:11.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}乌特雷德, 给我划! 啊!\N{\rEnglish}Uhtred, pull for me. Aah!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.24,0:45:15.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我去撒泡尿, 马上回来  - 他会回来的\N{\rEnglish}- I need to piss. I'll return. - He'll return.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.68,0:45:18.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}拉格纳? 拉格纳?\N{\rEnglish}Ragnar? Ragnar?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.44,0:45:34.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我很久没这么开心地笑过了\N{\rEnglish}I haven't laughed so much in a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.64,0:45:36.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那说明你活得不够痛快\N{\rEnglish}Then you haven't been living.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.64,0:45:40.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}或者像拉文说的, "明日我们便死"\N{\rEnglish}Or as ravn would say, "tomorrow we die."
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.20,0:45:42.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他什么时候说过这话?\N{\rEnglish}When did he ever say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.32,0:45:45.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你去劈柴的时候\N{\rEnglish}When you were out chopping wood.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.56,0:45:52.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我是真的要去撒尿\N{\rEnglish}Well, I actually do need to piss.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.12,0:45:56.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}哈哈, 你该做的是少喝点酒\N{\rEnglish}Ha, ha, what you need to do is to stop drinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.60,0:45:58.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}明天我们就要死了\N{\rEnglish}Tomorrow we die.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.64,0:46:07.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 他很高兴见到你   - 我也想他了\N{\rEnglish}- He's happy to see you. - I've missed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.84,0:46:13.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我想念你们俩\N{\rEnglish}I miss you both.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.72,0:46:23.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}她是你的妻子?\N{\rEnglish}Are you his wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.24,0:46:25.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我跟他在一起\N{\rEnglish}I'm with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.44,0:46:29.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 她漂亮吗? - 嗯\N{\rEnglish}- Is she beautiful? - Mm.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.16,0:46:33.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}她叫米尔德丝, 很漂亮\N{\rEnglish}Her name's mildrith. Yes, she is beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.24,0:46:39.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}她怀了我的孩子\N{\rEnglish}She carries my child.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.64,0:46:46.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是谁决定你们成婚的?\N{\rEnglish}Who decided you should marry?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.32,0:46:49.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}阿尔弗雷德\N{\rEnglish}Alfred.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.84,0:46:55.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我在威塞克斯得到了我想要的那片土地\N{\rEnglish}I have the land I asked for in wessex.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.40,0:47:01.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你向阿尔弗雷德宣誓效忠\N{\rEnglish}You swear an oath to Alfred.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.52,0:47:05.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你为阿尔弗雷德娶妻, 土地也是阿尔弗雷德赐给你的\N{\rEnglish}You marry for Alfred. You have land given to you by Alfred.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.44,0:47:07.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你的妻子怀了你的骨肉\N{\rEnglish}Your wife carries your child.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.40,0:47:11.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}可阿尔弗雷德竟然把你当人质献出去?\N{\rEnglish}And yet you're given up as a hostage by Alfred?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.52,0:47:13.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你是探子吗, 乌特雷德?\N{\rEnglish}Are you a spy, uhtred?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.36,0:47:20.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}一旦乌巴回来的风声传出, 我就得设法逃脱\N{\rEnglish}At the first sign of ubba returning, I am to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.28,0:47:26.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但我心里清楚, 乌巴一回来, 那些人质就会被杀\N{\rEnglish}But I know that when ubba returns, the hostages will be killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.28,0:47:29.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}阿尔弗雷德不喜欢我\N{\rEnglish}Alfred's not fond of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.60,0:47:31.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}拒绝他\N{\rEnglish}Refuse him.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.20,0:47:34.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}拒绝当人质, 加入我们\N{\rEnglish}Refuse to be a hostage. Join us.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.80,0:47:39.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我该问你的, 乌特雷德\N{\rEnglish}I should ask you, uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.44,0:47:42.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不是说结果会有什么不同, 但我该问你的\N{\rEnglish}Not that it matters, but I should ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.84,0:47:45.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}布丽达现在跟我在一起, 你有意见吗?\N{\rEnglish}Is it a problem to you that brida's with me now?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.72,0:47:50.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}哈, 没有, 我很高兴\N{\rEnglish}Ha, ha, no. I'm happy about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.16,0:47:53.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我发誓  - 好吧\N{\rEnglish}- I swear. - All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.12,0:47:56.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}再说她也不在乎你怎么想\N{\rEnglish}Not that she cares what you think.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.84,0:47:59.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}反正不管你同不同意我也会睡她, 不过...\N{\rEnglish}I would hump her regardless. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.44,0:48:01.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是带着...带着情意的\N{\rEnglish}With... with affection.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.64,0:48:04.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 也是经过我允许的     - 我知道\N{\rEnglish}- And with my permission. - I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.84,0:48:09.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你知道乌特雷德快当父亲了吗?\N{\rEnglish}Do you know uhtred's to be a father?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.80,0:48:16.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 什么时候? - 听说快了\N{\rEnglish}- When? - Soon, I'm told.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.08,0:48:20.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你想去看孩子出生?\N{\rEnglish}You would want to see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.88,0:48:24.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}想, 我希望能回去陪我的妻儿\N{\rEnglish}Yes. I hope to return to my wife and child.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.44,0:48:29.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}拉格纳\N{\rEnglish}Ragnar.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.44,0:48:34.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我会和你一起为父亲报仇, 基尔坦会付出代价的\N{\rEnglish}I'll be with you to avenge our father. Kjartan will pay.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.24,0:48:36.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你几个月前就该带着布丽达来找我了\N{\rEnglish}You should have joined me months ago with brida.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.12,0:48:38.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我宣过誓\N{\rEnglish}I'd sworn an oath.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.04,0:48:41.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}对一个烂透了的撒克逊王\N{\rEnglish}To a poxy Saxon king.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.52,0:48:44.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}乌巴要我的命, 我无处可去\N{\rEnglish}Ubba wanted me dead. There was nowhere else to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.44,0:48:46.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我一直在想那天晚上在林子里的事\N{\rEnglish}I've thought about that night in the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.92,0:48:50.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 你当时可以选择做撒克逊人还是丹麦人  - 不, 我已经宣过誓了\N{\rEnglish}- You had a choice to be Saxon or Dane. - No, I had sworn an oath.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.04,0:48:54.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你本该来找我的\N{\rEnglish}You should have joined me.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.92,0:48:57.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我会和你一起去杀基尔坦\N{\rEnglish}I'll be with you to kill kjartan.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.60,0:49:05.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我带你去教堂, 送你上床休息\N{\rEnglish}I will take you to the church, to your bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.08,0:49:35.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 怎么了? - 是个儿子, 夫人\N{\rEnglish}- What is it? - It's a son, lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.52,0:49:37.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}漂亮的小子\N{\rEnglish}A handsome boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.00,0:49:46.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你将是乌特雷德, 乌特雷德之子\N{\rEnglish}You will be uhtred, son of uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.96,0:49:57.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}早安，乌特雷德\N{\rEnglish}Good morning, uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.04,0:49:59.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}早安，神父\N{\rEnglish}Good morning, father.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.56,0:50:02.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}又下雨了\N{\rEnglish}Raining again.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.96,0:50:05.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}每天都一个样\N{\rEnglish}One day seems like the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.36,0:50:08.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是啊\N{\rEnglish}It does.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.44,0:50:12.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不过至少我们还活着，还能感受这雨\N{\rEnglish}Still, at least we're alive to feel it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.04,0:50:16.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你跟古思伦谈得怎么样?\N{\rEnglish}How are your conversations with guthrum?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.92,0:50:18.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他信天主了吗?\N{\rEnglish}Is he a Christian yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.72,0:50:21.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我相信时机快到了，真的\N{\rEnglish}I believe the time is near, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.96,0:50:26.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我常常让他一个人在教堂里静思\N{\rEnglish}I often leave him to contemplate alone in church.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.20,0:50:30.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}古思伦喜欢沉思的是战争和王国\N{\rEnglish}Guthrum likes to contemplate war and kingdoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.52,0:50:33.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}天国的荣光也等着他来分享\N{\rEnglish}The kingdom of heaven is his to share.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.88,0:50:35.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我已经告诉他了\N{\rEnglish}I've told him.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.04,0:50:38.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}一个人是可以改变的，乌特雷德\N{\rEnglish}A man can change, uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.92,0:50:44.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}前行吧，愿主赐福于你\N{\rEnglish}Onward. God bless you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.28,0:50:46.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}祝你度过美好的一天\N{\rEnglish}May you enjoy a good day.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.00,0:50:48.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}多谢，神父\N{\rEnglish}Thank you, father.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.76,0:50:53.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}祂是万王之王\N{\rEnglish}He is the king of kings.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.60,0:50:56.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}能够成就无比伟大的事\N{\rEnglish}Capable of great, great things.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.44,0:50:58.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}比如什么?\N{\rEnglish}Such as what?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.76,0:51:00.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}比如奇迹\N{\rEnglish}Such as miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.40,0:51:03.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}奇迹?\N{\rEnglish}Miracles?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.40,0:51:05.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}比如什么?\N{\rEnglish}Such as what?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.68,0:51:09.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}比如您，大人\N{\rEnglish}Such as you, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.60,0:51:12.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}您就是一个奇迹\N{\rEnglish}You are a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.28,0:51:18.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}祂让你刚强而不失仁慈\N{\rEnglish}He has made you strong yet merciful.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.92,0:51:20.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}祂...\N{\rEnglish}He has...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.60,0:51:24.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}让你自豪而不失谦逊\N{\rEnglish}Made you proud yet humble.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.56,0:51:27.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}祂让你渴望学习\N{\rEnglish}He has made you eager to learn.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.20,0:51:31.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}祂赐给你自由意志\N{\rEnglish}He has given you free will,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.44,0:51:36.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}希望你能鼓起勇气, 将祂置于一切之上\N{\rEnglish}hoping that you will find the courage to choose him above all else.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.52,0:51:40.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我相信, 我真心相信\N{\rEnglish}And I believe, I truly believe,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.44,0:51:42.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}祂会得到回报\N{\rEnglish}he will be rewarded.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.20,0:51:52.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我有消息要带给古思伦    - 他在教堂里\N{\rEnglish}- I have a message for guthrum. - He's in the church.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.72,0:52:10.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 大人, 我可以说吗  - 直说\N{\rEnglish}- Lord, may I speak? - Freely.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.96,0:52:13.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}乌巴和他的军队从爱尔兰回来了\N{\rEnglish}Ubba and his army have returned from Ireland.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.84,0:52:16.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他们正在北边的塞文河一带登岸\N{\rEnglish}They are coming ashore north of here at the severn.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.00,0:52:19.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我的舰队在哪儿?\N{\rEnglish}And my fleet is where?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.20,0:52:22.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}几天前已从伦敦出发, 快到了\N{\rEnglish}They left lundene several days ago and are nearly here.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.36,0:52:25.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}每一艘船都会到, 每一个人都会跟着你\N{\rEnglish}Every last ship will be here. Every man will be with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.64,0:52:27.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这是好消息\N{\rEnglish}That is good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.60,0:52:34.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我送你去你们的天堂\N{\rEnglish}I dispatch you to your heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.92,0:52:40.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不用谢我\N{\rEnglish}No need to thank me.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.16,0:52:57.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}神父\N{\rEnglish}Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.96,0:53:01.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}乌巴回来了?\N{\rEnglish}Ubba has returned?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.16,0:53:02.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他们说了吗?\N{\rEnglish}Did they say?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.36,0:53:10.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}弟兄们, 休战结束了\N{\rEnglish}Men, the peace is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.12,0:53:13.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}备战!\N{\rEnglish}Prepare for battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.92,0:53:25.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}把撒克逊人质全部杀掉\N{\rEnglish}The Saxon hostages, kill them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.76,0:53:30.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 抓住他! - 抓住他!\N{\rEnglish}- Catch him! - Get him.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.56,0:53:32.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}把他剁碎!\N{\rEnglish}Cut him to pieces!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.24,0:53:37.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}杀了他!\N{\rEnglish}Kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.64,0:53:56.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}放他走\N{\rEnglish}Leave him.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.24,0:53:58.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我说放他走!\N{\rEnglish}I say leave him!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.64,0:54:01.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}拉格纳\N{\rEnglish}Ragnar.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.28,0:54:05.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}请让开\N{\rEnglish}Please step aside.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.88,0:54:08.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你知道所有人质都得死\N{\rEnglish}You know all of the hostages have to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.00,0:54:10.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那就杀了他\N{\rEnglish}Then kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.68,0:54:13.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你尽管去杀他, 但你得先杀了我\N{\rEnglish}You're welcome to kill him. But you have to kill me first.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.12,0:54:16.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}没有这件事的话我会很开心的\N{\rEnglish}I could happily manage without this.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.80,0:54:21.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他是撒克逊人, 是叛徒, 是敌人\N{\rEnglish}He's a Saxon. He's a traitor. He's an enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.24,0:54:24.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那你要过去, 就得先杀了我\N{\rEnglish}Well, to get to him, you have to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.48,0:54:29.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我的手下不会跟着你走\N{\rEnglish}My men, they will not follow you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.32,0:54:43.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我最后再给你一次机会\N{\rEnglish}I will give you one last charity.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.04,0:54:47.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}放他走, 不给马\N{\rEnglish}Release him without a horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.96,0:54:59.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你没事吧?\N{\rEnglish}Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.76,0:55:02.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我不知道说什么好\N{\rEnglish}I have no words.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.52,0:55:05.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你走吧, 去看看你的孩子, 去\N{\rEnglish}You should go. Go and see your child. Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.92,0:55:10.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}好\N{\rEnglish}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.84,0:55:12.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我会找到你的\N{\rEnglish}I'll be with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.16,0:55:15.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你们两个都是\N{\rEnglish}Both of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.98,0:55:17.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
